text: Click on Parts Manager. Click pending Invoices. Click on invoice. Fill in details on screen that comes up, Invoice number, total and date.
Click Creditor
Click PartsCheck
Next, click Import from PartsCheck. This will import from PartsCheck that the part has been received.This will update the Quote.
Click Creditor. Click PartsCheck
Click Import fom PartsCheck. This will update the quote to have the received status updated

Check the ABN from the regisration form. Go to the ABN Lookup website at https://abr.business.gov.au/. Enter-in the ABN provided. Make sure that it is a registered ABN number and that it relates to the shop name that they have listed. If it is not registered, you cannot proceed to verify the shop. Take note that not all ABNs display the trading name.
Google search the business address. Make sure that it is a business address and not a home address. If it is a home address you will not be able to verify the shop.
Do a website search. Search company name into a google page or Facebook to see what comes up.This can show that companies are closed, or give you an idea of shop size

Call the Customer and verify the following: Email Address, Contact person, Phone number, and the Quote Package. While talking to the customer verify all details that they have entered in the registration form, updating and changing any that are not correct. We need to make sure that all these details are correct. Update any that aren't.

Enter in Date verified. Verified date is for reporting.Use US date format. Use the '--  symbol. Change status with the drop down arrow to  verified. Next, select the Quote Package from the drop down box. Without doing this step the quote won't be able to be sent and bought back into the Quote Package. If they don't have a quote package you don't need to select any. For AutoQuote you need to make sure that the associations are set up first before switching on the orders

Click in Maximum Prefered suppliers. Change the preferred suppliers to 10 (doing more then 10 suppliers distorts the screen). For AutoSync Order -select yes from the drop down box . Set Auto Sync Order to Yes (except if it is Auto-Quote). Auto Quote needs to have the associations set up before turning on auto sync orders. Click Global Roaming to Yes.
For IBody Customers ( Credits ) - Make sure to set the Bypass Supplier Suth to No (only for IBody Shop customers)

Complete notes of the following field and enter into CM Panel and Zendesk- ABN CHECK, PHONE CHECK, QUOTE PACKAGE, SHOP GRADING, FIND US METHOD, SPECIAL NOTES. Shop grading can be a guess and must be updated later once quoting through the system. Entering it into both systems allows everyone to see where the shop is up to.
To add a Supplier, enter the applicable client into CM Panel. Click Edit
To assign the suppliers click the 'Preferred Suppliers' tab.

Click Assign Supplier to all Makes. Alternatively, click 'Add' next to the applicable vehicle make. Repairers Choice to specify which supplier that they use for each Brand. Selecting all makes for Suppliers that do multiple makes, can put multiple
Select the applicable supplier from the drop-down menu. Once you have selected the supplier,
Click Assign then Click Refresh
The supplier has now been added to the clients preferred supplier list and the applicable makes they supply.
Enter the applicable client into CM Panel Click Edit
Select the Preferred Suppliers tab
Select Remove Supplier from All Makes
Select the applicable supplier from the drop-down menu
Click Remove. Click Refresh
The supplier has now been removed from the clients preferred supplier list
Click on Supplier. When you have multiple OEM suppliers per make, PatsCheck will push the one with the highest star rating to the top and be automatically selected.

In the Supplier put in 2 on the tier level for the one that you have as a second pick. Click Update. We tier so that the customer has their first pick selected all the time but are still able to select the other supplier if needed.

For Business Manager integration, you will need to book a time with the developers or Cecily or Joyce to do the integration through Jira.

Make sure the box next to Parts Order is ticked. This is to make sure the orders update.

Use AnyDesk or TeamViewer to remotely access the customer's computer. TeamViewer link can be accessed via "My PartsCheck" menu in top right corner once logged in or via bottom of main webpage.
Login to PartsCheck. Enter user information in the pop-up window. This allows individuals to be notified of their quotes being returned

Adding User - Type Surname. Enter Estimator. Type position/role of staff member. Type Email address. Type mobile number. Click Create User. Adding this information allows you to keep track of who is working on or has completed the quote. It also gives you the option to select a user to be notified when the quote is ready, or, in the case of a direct purchase, to receive updates when the item is on its way.
User Created - Check and Amend if Required. Click on User up the top.
Click Edit. To delete the user - click delete
On the home screen, click GET PRICE. This step begins the process of requesting a quote from your supplier.
Or Click on Send Quotes

If sending from a quote package, click FROM QUOTE PACKAGE, then select the quote you want to send. Your quote package automatically fills in the details for this step, so you don't need to re-enter any information.
If no quote package exists, manually start a new quote by clicking NEW QUOTE

Enter or confirm all required information. Complete every field marked with a red asterisk (*). When finished, click NEXT to continue. Comments entered here will appear to the supplier. Try to be as detailed as possible. Completing this step carefully helps suppliers accurately quote the parts you need. Clear and complete information reduces the chance of errors, follow-up questions, and delays in receiving your quote.

Select, add, or edit images as needed. When finished, click NEXT to continue. Upload clear, high-quality images that suppliers can use to accurately identify the required parts. Well-lit and focused images will help minimise quoting errors and ensure faster and more accurate responses.
Click NEXT to bypass the Build Quote step. This step is only visible when creating a manual quote. Should only be used if creating a manual quote but not necessary.

Enter the parts you require, listing one part per line. If the quote was created from a quote package, the parts will already be populated for you. List one part per line, provide accurate and complete part descriptions, review all part entries carefully, check pre-filled parts if using a quote package, and keep part entries organised and accurate. Following these steps ensures suppliers clearly understand your request, reduces errors or misquotes, speeds up response times, and improves the accuracy and availability of the parts quoted. It helps you get the right parts faster and at the best possible price.

Tick SELECT ALL to select all part types (OEM, Used, Aftermarket or Reconditioned). Then click NEXT. Selecting all part types ensures your quote request covers every available part option from your selected suppliers — OEM, parallel, aftermarket, recycled, and reconditioned. This increases both your chances of securing the best price and sourcing available parts quickly. Selecting all part types allows suppliers to quote across all available options, helping you source parts faster and often at a better price. Limiting part types can reduce availability and delay your quoting process.

To select suppliers, use your 'preferred supplier list' or scroll down to choose from the suggested suppliers. Click “Add Temporarily” to select a supplier for this quote only, or click “Add to Preferred” to save them for future quotes. Once your suppliers are selected, click NEXT to continue. Select one OEM dealer and up to nine additional suppliers, aiming to send your quote request to all ten where possible to maximise part availability, pricing options, and supplier response speed. Sending your quote to the maximum number of suppliers increases your chances of receiving faster responses, better pricing, and higher part availability. It also gives suppliers more opportunity to compete for your business, which can result in better overall outcomes for your quote.
Click in Search Supplier to find the supplier that you are looking for. To look up Suppliers that you can’t find easily

Click Change Tier. Having tier's allocated means that you can have multiple OEM suppliers that will come up to select. If you do not have them set in tier’s it means that whichever Supplier has the highest star rating will come up first. This can cause the customers to get frustrated as it keeps changing
Select which Tier that you need them to be. Click OK

Select the time by which you would like your quote prices completed. Choose a standard time frame by ticking a time box, or select “Urgent” from the drop-down menu if a faster response is needed. Once selected, click SUBMIT to send your request. To ensure quality and efficiency, select a suitable response time so suppliers can meet your required turnaround. If your quote has many line items, allow additional time for suppliers to respond thoroughly before clicking SUBMIT to send your request. If suppliers miss the cutoff time, they can’t submit their prices. Allowing more time — especially for larger quotes — helps ensure you receive complete and competitive responses.
Review all information carefully. When you are ready to proceed, click OK to send your quote to the selected suppliers.
Click Check Price

After sending, the quote will appear in the Active Quotes screen, where it will stay until prices are received from the suppliers. Monitor supplier responses through status icons: a green tick means prices have been returned, a yellow tick indicates a partial or different response (hover over it for details), and a red cross shows no response or that the supplier missed the deadline — helping you quickly track quote progress and follow up efficiently. Understanding the status icons allows you to quickly assess supplier responses, identify any missing or delayed quotes, and take prompt action to follow up, ensuring you keep the quoting process moving efficiently.
Once prices are all received back. Click Open on the Quote
Click Rules Set

Mark up Settings. Show the customer how to create rules that they can use. Add Rules that align with Business goals. Customers can set a default rule. Making sure that they are getting the allocated mark ups that they are entitled to.
Click Quick Selection. To save time the customer can select from the drop down - Best Profit and it will select those parts for you
Click Grid View
Click List View

Supplier Information. If you hover your mouse over the supplier icon - it will let you see the supplier phone number, delivery and the price expiry. This is important for the customer to be able to see when the price expires and the supplier information
Supplier Comment. The "!" Mark in the grey corner of the price shows that the supplier has left a comment. Customer could miss out on key information from the supplier
Green Flame. Part numbers match between the parallel supplier and the OEM supplier

Purple Flame - "Aftermarket certified parts" refers to replacement car parts that are not manufactured by the original equipment manufacturer (OEM) but have been tested and certified by a recognized organization, like the Certified Automotive Parts Association (CAPA), to meet specific quality standards, ensuring they are comparable to the original part in terms of fit, form, and function, making them a reliable and safe option for consumers; essentially, it means the aftermarket part has undergone rigorous testing to prove its quality is on par with the OEM part
Supplier adding Parts. If the supplier thinks that extra parts are needed, they will add the parts and they will come through as orange. This is where the supplier can add freight to the order.
When it appears red it means that the Part has been deleted in the quote package
Optional Part. An optional part is when the supplier has an alternate part – e.g. used. You will only be able to select one of the parts.
Selecting Parts. When selecting the parts you can click on the supplier icon at the top and it will select all the parts that they have priced.
Or you can select each part individually by clicking on it.

Modify Calculator. Once the price is selected you can click on the modify calculator to modify the price. This is up to the customer to use to get the best profit that they can. Changing the prices in PartsCheck will update the Quote Package.
[Images]

Hover the mouse over the price for Part Information. When hovering the mouse over the price it will bring u a box with the information on the part. This will show you the Mark-Up and Profit. Comments that the Supplier has left.

Profit Calculator. Profit calculator will show the profit that you will make if you select those parts, you can select other parts and use the modify calculator to make sure that you are getting the best profit off the parts
Save Prices. Once you have selected the parts that you want, click save

Click Confirm Parts. This will Update your Quote Package with the Part numbers and prices. If you do not want it to update the quote package untick the box and press confirm. Tick not in box means that the settings are not set up for auto sync

Obtain the customer's phone number by accessing their account in the CM Panel under Setup Client to avoid calling incorrect number. Always obtain the customer's phone number directly from the CM Panel under Setup Client, as numbers stored in other systems like Pipedrive or Zendesk may be outdated or incorrect, ensuring you contact the correct person without delays.

Ask the customer for their TeamViewer ID and password. If they do not have TeamViewer installed, instruct them to download it, or use AnyDesk as an alternative. Ensure to note down ID and password. Writing down the customer's details as they read them out helps prevent errors, ensures accuracy when connecting remotely, and avoids delays caused by incorrect information.
Once logged into PartsCheck, enter the quote number in the search bar to locate the quote, or click Check Price and find the quote under SAVED QUOTES. Click Open to view the quote.
Carefully review the previously selected part lines. Deselect any items the client no longer wishes to order, confirm the correct parts remain selected, and then click SAVE to continue.

Advise the customer that they can review their selected parts and access reports for List Price, Cost Price, and Unavailable Parts from this page to confirm accuracy before proceeding. The customer can send them off to the Insurance assessor.

Choose the appropriate Preferred Supply Date, add any relevant Supply Notes for the supplier, and then click PURCHASE to finalise the order. Entering the correct Supply Date ensures parts arrive when needed, limiting delays and preventing overstock in the parts warehouse. Adding clear Supply Notes helps suppliers meet specific requirements, and ensuring Autosync is selected allows for seamless data transfer into quote packages for faster processing. Entering clear Supply Notes ensures that suppliers receive important information, such as ETA requirements, helping them meet your delivery expectations and reducing the risk of delays or miscommunication.
Click the Orders tab to view and manage the order you have just completed.

Orders Screen - Monitoring order status icons helps track supplier progress: a green eye means the supplier has viewed the order, a green truck indicates the parts have been dispatched, and a yellow truck shows a partial shipment. Checking the ETA date provides expected delivery timing, helping manage parts arrival and reduce delays. Tracking the order status through icons and ETA dates allows the customer to quickly see the progress of their orders, helping them manage expectations and plan repairs or work more efficiently.

When a supplier requests authority for a back-ordered item, click on the Orders tab, then click Authority Req. This will display all orders requiring your authorisation for back-ordered parts. Customers should approve back-order requests as soon as possible, as suppliers will not process or dispatch the part until approval is given; any delay in approval will directly delay the receipt of the part and extend repair times. Authorising back-ordered parts promptly ensures suppliers can proceed with sourcing and dispatching delayed items, helping to minimise downtime and keep jobs progressing without unnecessary hold-ups.

Click on the dropdown box and select either Approve or Reject, depending on the required action. It's important the customer is aware that once a back-ordered part is approved, it cannot be cancelled or returned without discussing directly with supplier, ensuring they make a fully informed decision before proceeding.
Once you have made your selection, enter your name and click Apply to finalise the action.

Click Add Item
Fill in required information. Suppliers will add freight etc. This is where you can add it so that the invoice matches. Don't add extra parts in this section. Its only for freight.

Enter invoice details in far-right pop up- Click update- Making sure the invoice number, date and total is always the same as the paper invoice provided. You can have the auto sync option turned to enable which will allow it to take the data packed back into your BMS package or disabled which will show items have been receipted but not reflect into BMS.
Rate supplier. Click OK to finalise receiving

To show the customers how to track the parts, the orders screen uses color code when parts are receitped. Yellow tick means that the parts have been partially receipted. Green tick means that the parts are fully receipted
To change the price Click on the pencil. This is a must to make sure that PartsCheck has the same amount as the invoice from the supplier
You can then change the amounts to match the amount on the invoice. Once changed click Update.

Click ORDERS. Click the purchase order in PartsCheck or Use the search bar at the top right of the homescreen. You can only credit an item once it has been receipted – so ensure that has been done first. You may need to credit an item back if its incorrect, broken or no longer needed
Click 'CREDIT REQUEST'. Select the items to be credited by ticking the square box. Click UPDATE.
Enter your name and select the reason for the credit. This will let the supplier know who is requesting the credit. It will also keep a record for your business.
Click OK to create the credit request. This will submit your credit request.
Credit Management Screen. Preview Credit List
Open Credit
Type credit note
Authorised by, dropdown or new staff member
Save credit
How to Finalise a Credit. Re-open credit.
Mark as completed. Save changes. Optional - Print Credit
Exit from screen
Confirm with Line strike through Credit. Final check - Credit is removed from list
In Crashzone. Click PartsCheck. The status will change from Ordered to Credited

sub_process: Bringing credit back into Business Manager
text: Open the purchase order in BM. There is a message - Please Process Credit Request. Click on Create Credit Note. It will automatically have the parts credited selected. Click OK to post the credit note.

To complete training off-site. Two-way view and communication for effective training and illustration.Use Anydesk or Teamviewer software to remote access the customers computer. Customer must have access to internet. Anydesk or TeamViewer to be downloaded prior to training
There are two ways to access 'Reporting' - Select REPORTING on dashboard and Select My PartsCheck>Reporting. Reporting provides additional data on part sales and credits
Reporting from'My PartsCheck'
Detailed purchase Analysis - There are several steps to this task. Broken down into smaller sub-steps. To provide a detailed analysis of purchases.

Detailed analysis of sales parts margins by supplier and make - Set Targets. Select date range. Select supplier, date range and margin%. This is optional for repairers they wish to assess suppliers that have agreements or contracts. Predominately an MSO. Supplier must be on preferred supplier list. Broken down by supplier and makes they trade.
Filter by Suppliers, vehicle make, part type, supplier type.

To analyse reasons for credits. Credit Comparison - Credit Analysis report shows you your credit return rate per supplier Pie graph - credit return types. Linear graph by supplier. Note: Only top 20% by volume.

A detailed analysis of all credit requests for chosen date range. Credit Requests by Date Range. Select date range - generate CSV: SQLQuery - creditrequestID,purchaserName,supplierName,vehMake,mthyr_creditRequested,date_creditRequested,purchaseOderNr,originalInvoiceNumber,requestStatus,requestReason,itemDescription,creditNoteN,itemQuotedPrice,supplierPartNr,creditRequestBy,rejectReason,isCreditCompleted,isCreditCompleteddate

A detailed analysis of sales lost per supplier. To identify if Parts Manager is selecting by Supplier over price. Identify the negative figures over positive figures to make better choices for increased profits.. Items Lost per Supplier. Select supplier, date range – generate CSV. SQLQuery: quoteNr,vehMake,vehModel,vehseries,vehYear,partDescn,quotedSupplier,quoteditemType,quoteditemComment,quotedPrice,otherSupplier,otherPartType,otherItemComment,otherPrice,otherPricevarance,is,PurchasedFromSupplier,isPurchasedFromOther,nsReasonText,quotedate,supplierOrderdate,OtherOrdereddate.

Detailed analysis of all items purchased within a date range, as well as the credit status of parts where a credit request has been raised. All Items Purchased for Period. Select date, Range, (optional) Summary Only - generate CSV. SQL query - Suppliername,cnt_purchaseOrders,

When a supplier does not quote on your request for quote, a reason must be selected. This report shows all parts where no parts were available, and the reason. Note: Only suppliers where you have purchased items are listed- No Parts Available Per Supplier. Select supplier, quote start date, quote end date. SQL query - supplierName,quoteNR,vehMake,vehModel,vehSeries,vehYear,noPartsReason,partDescn
Onboarding Repairers on PartsCheck: Onboarding is triggerred when a customer registers on PartsCheck website.

Step 1. The trainer confirms the Client Information. Check the ABN on ABN Lookup, Business Address, Information from the Rego form, and searching the Website. This procedure is detailed in  JI_103_01.

Step 2. The trainer Gives an overview. Call customer to present PowerPoint. (TBA) - explaining PartsCheck functionalities, its benefit to the customer, and its interface with specific quoting package. This procedure is detailed in JI_103_02.

Step 3. The trainer verifies customer details: Verify Email Adress, Contact person, Phone number, and Quote Package.  Update CM panel verifying details and set up. Enter Notes into CM Panel -  Zendesk. This procedure is detailed in JI_103_03.
Step 4. The trainer discuss preferred suppliers with customer:  Update PSL in CM Panel. Preferred supplier form will be emailed with Welcome Email. This procedure is detailed in  JI_103_04.

Step 5. Integrating PartsCheck with the quote package:  Flexiquote - enter in hash, AutoQuote - Book integration with Development team, BM - Book integration with Development team, IBodyShop - Email Ibody, Crashzone - enter in hash. This procedure is detailed in  JI_103_05
Step 6.  Send Vision 6 Email: Send Welcome Email through Vision 6. This procedure is detailed in JI_103_06
